name: I Flew The STRANGEST Transatlantic Route...
description:
About three years ago, I made a video talking about one of the most unique transatlantic flights that Canada gets - Condor's seasonal service between Frankfurt and Whitehorse, Yukon.

In September 2022, I finally got to fly that very route!

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Airline: Condor (CFG/DE)
Aircraft: Boeing 767-300ER (B763)
Flight Number: DE2426
Seat: 8K (Premium Economy)
Livery: Old (Post-Thomas Cook)
Engines: 2x Pratt & Whitney PW4060
Registration: D-ABUA
Route: Frankfurt (FRA) - Whitehorse (YXY)
Callsign: CONDOR 426
Runway used: 25C (FRA) - 14R (YXY)
Date filmed: September 2022
